<h3>Escape table</h3>

<p>Special XML characters must be escaped using the corresponding entities. Only the <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/#sec-predefined-ent">five standard predefined XML entities</a> must be escaped, other entities may be used but are not mandatory. The escaped characters are determined by this table:</p>

<table border="1">
 <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Unescaped</th>
      <th>Escaped</th>
      <th>Reason for escaping</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>

    <tr>
      <td>&amp;</td>
      <td>&amp;amp;</td>
      <td>This is the escaping character itself used to start a new entity.</td>
    </tr>

    <tr>
      <td>&lt;</td>
      <td>&amp;lt;</td>
      <td>Used by XML to start a new tag.</td>
    </tr>

    <tr>
      <td>&gt;</td>
      <td>&amp;gt;</td>
      <td>Used by XML to close a tag.</td>
    </tr>

   <tr>
      <td>&quot;</td>
      <td>&amp;quot;</td>
      <td>Used by XML to delimit an attribute value.</td>
    </tr>
 
   <tr>
      <td>&apos;</td>
      <td>&amp;apos;</td>
      <td>Alternative character to delimit an attribute value.</td>
    </tr> 

   </tbody>
  </thead>
</table>

<p>Any output generated by the <code>mwetoolkit</code> will have these characters escaped as well.</p>



<h3>Code comments</h3>

<p>We use the <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/#sec-comments">standard XML format</a> for comments, delimited by "&lt;!-- comment --&gt;".</p>




